Welcome to another edition of SNL - its been some time !!!! The news meanwhile has been good in SOME in part - but tragic mostly.
The recent spate of violence against women again have shown us that we have not found any solutions to this issue - while politicians have used the opportunity every time - to play the blame game - nothing much real comes out of it. 
Are we going to look for hard answers now or are happy finder-pointing?

comments.text:
Potential Rapists.

I recently came across a subreddit where members are openly discussing and endorsing sexual violence against women. The comments are filled with horrifying statements like "zabardasti chodunga" and "bina consent ke," which clearly indicate an intent to engage in non-consensual acts. This is not just toxic, it's criminal behavior being normalized and encouraged in these discussions. Usually they pass these comments towards actresses.

We seriously need to do something about this. If we all start reporting this subreddit, we can help get it banned. Let's not let this kind of disgusting behavior slide.

It's deeply disturbing that these individuals are openly plotting sexual violence, disguising their intent by not explicitly using the word "rape," but their messages are clear and dangerous. We must not allow these individuals to continue spreading their misogynistic, violent rhetoric.

And that subreddit is r/indianmenlockerroom.
